git init:
it is used to create empty repo inside a folder structure.


Staging environment=>
git add .=>to push all your files to staging environment 
git add index.html =>to push one file at a time.


commit environment=>
git commit -m "Commit message"

git and github life saviour for many developers



1.create a new repository
new button by providing repo name with other details
2.


git config --global user.name "Sam Smith"
git config --global user.email sam@example.com

we are telling github that i m the owner of this account& use this
credential to push all the changes globally

3.creta git init command for initial repo 
4.Adding of files
git add filename 
git add *
(stage or stash)

5.
git commit -m "added this functionality"
(commit environment)

6.
set the branch 
git branch branchname 

7.
set the remote connect

git remote add origin urlofgithub 

if you get fatal error:
git remote rm origin 

8.
git push -u origin main 


















